
======================================================================
  Part 1: MINIMAL MODEL PRIMARIES = TRIANGULAR NUMBERS
======================================================================

Virasoro minimal model M(p, p+1) where p = m+2:
  Central charge: c(p) = 1 - 6/(p(p+1))
  Primary fields: (p-1)*p/2 = T_{p-1} (triangular numbers!)

    p   M(p,p+1)            c   #prim    = T_k  notes
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    3 M(3,4)           1/2       3 = T_2    KEY2  [c: num=unit den=KEY1]
    4 M(4,5)          7/10       6 = T_3    h(G2)  [c: num=H_forb_1 den=V(Pet)]
    5 M(5,6)           4/5      10 = T_4    V(Pet)  [c:  den=KEY_SUM]
    6 M(6,7)           6/7      15 = T_5    C(6,2)  [c: num=h(G2) den=H_forb_1]
    7 M(7,8)         25/28      21 = T_6    H_forb_2  [c:  den=dim(SO(8))]
    8 M(8,9)         11/12      28 = T_7    dim(SO(8))  [c:  den=h(E6)]
    9 M(9,10)         14/15      36 = T_8    |Phi+(E6)|  [c: num=dim(G2) den=C(6,2)]
   10 M(10,11)         52/55      45 = T_9    C(10,2)  [c:  den=C(11,2)]
   11 M(11,12)         21/22      55 = T_10   C(11,2)  [c: num=H_forb_2]
   12 M(12,13)         25/26      66 = T_11   h(G2)*11
   13 M(13,14)         88/91      78 = T_12   dim(E6)  [c:  den=N(f(omega))]
   14 M(14,15)         34/35      91 = T_13   N(f(omega))
   15 M(15,16)         39/40     105 = T_14   C(15,2)
   16 M(16,17)       133/136     120 = T_15   |BI|
   17 M(17,18)         50/51     136 = T_16   
   18 M(18,19)         56/57     153 = T_17   [c: num=f(10)]
   19 M(19,20)       187/190     171 = T_18   
   20 M(20,21)         69/70     190 = T_19   
   21 M(21,22)         76/77     210 = T_20   
   22 M(22,23)       250/253     231 = T_21   
   23 M(23,24)         91/92     253 = T_22   [c: num=N(f(omega))]
   24 M(24,25)        99/100     276 = T_23   

CROWN JEWELS:
  M(5,6): 10 = V(Petersen) primary fields!
  M(7,8): 21 = H_forb_2 primary fields!
  M(9,10): 36 = |Phi+(E6)| primary fields!
  M(13,14): 78 = dim(E6) primary fields!
  M(10,11): 45 = T_9 = KEY2^2 * KEY_SUM
  M(12,13): 66 = h(G2) * 11

======================================================================
  Part 2: THE ADE CLASSIFICATION OF MODULAR INVARIANTS
======================================================================

For each minimal model M(p, p+1), the modular invariant
partition functions are classified by ADE Dynkin diagrams!

The classification:
  A-type: exists for ALL p >= 3 (the diagonal invariant)
  D-type: exists when p is even (p >= 6)
  E_6: exists at p = 12 (so M(12,13))
  E_7: exists at p = 18 (so M(18,19))
  E_8: exists at p = 30 (so M(30,31))

TOURNAMENT CONNECTIONS:
  E_6 invariant at p = 12 = h(E6)
  E_7 invariant at p = 18 = h(E7)
  E_8 invariant at p = 30 = h(E8)

  THE ADE MODULAR INVARIANTS OCCUR EXACTLY AT p = Coxeter numbers!
  This is the Cappelli-Itzykson-Zuber classification.

  M(12,13) [E6 invariant]: c = 25/26 = 0.961538, #primaries = 66
    66 = h(G2)*11
    = 2 * 3 * 11
  M(18,19) [E7 invariant]: c = 56/57 = 0.982456, #primaries = 153
    = 3^2 * 17
  M(30,31) [E8 invariant]: c = 154/155 = 0.993548, #primaries = 435
    = 3 * 5 * 29

  E6 at p=12: #primaries = 66 = 2*3*11 = h(G2)*11
  E7 at p=18: #primaries = 153 = 9*17 = KEY2^2 * 17
  E8 at p=30: #primaries = 435 = 3*5*29 = KEY2*KEY_SUM*(h(E8)-1)

======================================================================
  Part 3: CONFORMAL DIMENSIONS h_{r,s} AND TOURNAMENT NUMBERS
======================================================================

In M(p, p+1), the conformal dimensions are:
  h_{r,s} = ((p+1)*r - p*s)^2 - 1) / (4*p*(p+1))
  where 1 <= r <= p-1, 1 <= s <= p, r*s <= p*(p-1)/2

M(5,6) — the V(Petersen) model (10 primaries):

  Kac table h_{r,s}:
        s=       1  s=       2  s=       3  s=       4  s=       5
  r=1         0                                        
  r=2       2/5      1/40                              
  r=3       7/5     21/40      1/15                    
  r=4         3      13/8       2/3       1/8          

  Distinct conformal dimensions: ['0', '1/40', '1/15', '1/8', '2/5', '21/40', '2/3', '7/5', '13/8', '3']
  = [0.0, 0.025, 0.06666666666666667, 0.125, 0.4, 0.525, 0.6666666666666666, 1.4, 1.625, 3.0]

  h = 3 = KEY2

