======================================================================
  Part 5: THE VERLINDE FORMULA AND QUANTUM DIMENSIONS
======================================================================

The Verlinde formula computes fusion coefficients from S-matrix:
  N_{ij}^k = sum_l S_{il} S_{jl} S_{kl}^* / S_{0l}

For M(p, p+1), the S-matrix has size (p-1)(p)/2 × (p-1)(p)/2

M(3,4) = Ising model (KEY2 primaries):
  Fields: 1 (h=0), epsilon (h=1/2=1/KEY1), sigma (h=1/16)

  S-matrix:
  S = (1/2) * [[1, 1, sqrt(2)],
                [1, 1, -sqrt(2)],
                [sqrt(2), -sqrt(2), 0]]

  sqrt(2) = sqrt(KEY1)
  The Ising S-matrix involves sqrt(KEY1)!

Quantum dimensions d_i = S_{0i} / S_{00}:
  d_1 = 1 (identity)
  d_epsilon = S_{0,eps}/S_{00} = 1
  d_sigma = S_{0,sigma}/S_{00} = sqrt(2) = sqrt(KEY1)

  Total quantum dimension: D^2 = sum d_i^2 = 1 + 1 + 2 = 4 = KEY1^2
  D = 2 = KEY1

M(5,6) = 3-state Potts model (V(Petersen) = 10 primaries):
  Central charge: c = 4/5 = KEY1^2/KEY_SUM

  This is the critical point of the 3=KEY2 state Potts model!
  The number of Potts states = KEY2
  The number of primary fields = V(Petersen) = 10

  Quantum dimensions involve phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 (golden ratio)
  sqrt(5) = sqrt(KEY_SUM)
  The golden ratio = (1 + sqrt(KEY_SUM))/KEY1

======================================================================
  Part 6: THE c = 1 BARRIER
======================================================================

As p -> infinity, the minimal model central charges approach:
  c = 1 - 6/(p(p+1)) -> 1

  c = 1 is a critical barrier — beyond it:
  - The representation theory changes qualitatively
  - The Kac determinant has different structure
  - The theory is no longer 'minimal'

Approach to c=1:
  p=  5: c = 0.80000000, 1-c = 6/   30 = 0.20000000
  p= 10: c = 0.94545455, 1-c = 6/  110 = 0.05454545
  p= 20: c = 0.98571429, 1-c = 6/  420 = 0.01428571
  p= 30: c = 0.99354839, 1-c = 6/  930 = 0.00645161
  p= 50: c = 0.99764706, 1-c = 6/ 2550 = 0.00235294
  p=100: c = 0.99940594, 1-c = 6/10100 = 0.00059406

  At p = h(E8) = 30: c = 1 - 6/930 = 1 - 1/155
  = 154/155
  154 = 2 * 7 * 11 = KEY1 * H_forb_1 * 11
  155 = 5 * 31 = KEY_SUM * (h(E8)+1)

The deficit function delta(p) = 6/(p(p+1)) = 6*(1/p - 1/(p+1)):
  This is a TELESCOPING sum!
  Sum from p=3 to infinity = 6/3 - lim 6/(p+1) = 2 - 0 = 2 = KEY1

  Sum of ALL deficits = KEY1 = 2
  This means: the 'total central charge room' in minimal models = KEY1

======================================================================
  Part 7: FUSION CATEGORIES AND (2,3) STRUCTURE
======================================================================

Each minimal model M(p,p+1) gives a fusion category C_p.
The fusion rules form a ring (the Verlinde ring).

The rank of the fusion category = #primaries = T_{p-1}

Fusion categories with rank in tournament vocabulary:
  rank    3 =            KEY2 from M(3,4)
  rank    6 =           h(G2) from M(4,5)
