  rank   78 =         dim(E6) from M(13,14)
  rank   91 =     N(f(omega)) from M(14,15)
  rank  105 =         C(15,2) from M(15,16)
  rank  120 =            |BI| from M(16,17)

The Frobenius-Perron dimensions of M(p,p+1):
  FP-dim = p*(p+1)/4 * csc^2(pi/(p+1)) * ... (complicated)

Total FP-dimension D^2 of fusion category:
  M(3,4): c=0.5000, D^2 = 4.000000, #prim = 3
  M(4,5): c=0.7000, D^2 = 14.472136, #prim = 6
