======================================================================
  Part 8: THE MODULAR TENSOR CATEGORY PERSPECTIVE
======================================================================

Each minimal model gives a MODULAR TENSOR CATEGORY (MTC).
The MTC has a topological S-matrix satisfying:
  S^2 = C (charge conjugation)
  (ST)^3 = p_+ * S^2 (the ribbon relation)

  where T = diagonal matrix of exp(2pi*i*h_j)
  and p_+ = exp(2pi*i*c/8) (the anomaly)

Anomaly c/8 mod 1 for minimal models:
  M(3,4): c/8 = 1/16 = 0.062500
  M(4,5): c/8 = 7/80 = 0.087500
  M(5,6): c/8 = 1/10 = 0.100000
  M(6,7): c/8 = 3/28 = 0.107143
  M(7,8): c/8 = 25/224 = 0.111607
  M(8,9): c/8 = 11/96 = 0.114583
  M(9,10): c/8 = 7/60 = 0.116667
  M(10,11): c/8 = 13/110 = 0.118182
  M(12,13): c/8 = 25/208 = 0.120192
  M(18,19): c/8 = 7/57 = 0.122807
  M(30,31): c/8 = 77/620 = 0.124194

  For M(30,31) [E8 invariant]: c/8 = (1 - 6/930)/8 = 924/(8*930)
  = 77/620 = 0.12419355
  Numerator: 77, Denominator: 620

