STUNNING: T_4 = 10 = V(Petersen) = T(4) in (2,3)-operad
  The 4th triangular number = the 4th (2,3)-tree count!
  T_k and T(k) agree at k=4!

  T_1=1=T(1), T_2=3=T(3)? No, T_2=3 but T(2)=1
  T_3=6, T(3)=3: no match
  T_4=10, T(4)=10: MATCH!
  Is this a coincidence? Or is there structure?

Comparison T_k (triangular) vs T(k) ((2,3)-trees):
  k= 1: T_k =      1, T(k) =      1, ratio = 1.0000 MATCH!
  k= 2: T_k =      3, T(k) =      1, ratio = 3.0000 
