======================================================================
  Part 11: THE FIBONACCI ANYON MODEL AND (2,3)
======================================================================

The Fibonacci anyon model is the simplest non-abelian anyon theory.
It arises from M(4,5) at level k=3 (or SU(2) Chern-Simons at k=3).

Properties:
  Number of anyons: 2 = KEY1
  Quantum dimensions: 1 and phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 = (1+sqrt(KEY_SUM))/KEY1
  Total quantum dimension: D^2 = 1 + phi^2 = 2 + phi = 2.618034
    = (3+sqrt(5))/2 = (KEY2+sqrt(KEY_SUM))/KEY1

  Central charge: c = 14/5 = dim(G2)/KEY_SUM
  (Note: this is the coset c = c_{SU(2)_3} = 3*2/(2+3) = 6/5... 
   Actually the Fibonacci anyon has c = 14/5 = 2.8 in the topological theory)

  Fusion rules: tau x tau = 1 + tau (Fibonacci rule!)
  The fusion coefficient N_{tau,tau}^tau = 1
  The fusion coefficient N_{tau,tau}^1 = 1

  F-matrix (pentagon equation):
    F = [[1/phi,        1/sqrt(phi)],
         [1/sqrt(phi), -1/phi      ]]
    = [[0.618034, 0.786151],
       [0.786151, -0.618034]]

  det(F) = -1/phi^2 + 1/phi = -1/(phi+1) + 1/phi = ...
  det(F) = -1.000000
  = -1 (the F-matrix has determinant -1!)

  phi = 1.6180339887
  phi^2 = phi + 1 = 2.6180339887
  phi^5 = 11.0901699437 ≈ 11.09
  phi^10 = 122.991869 ≈ 122.99 ≈ |BI| + KEY2

======================================================================
  Part 12: GRAND SYNTHESIS: CFT IS THE (2,3) UNIVERSE IN DISGUISE
======================================================================

======================================================================
  CONFORMAL FIELD THEORY = THE (2,3) UNIVERSE INCARNATE
======================================================================

1. MINIMAL MODELS: #primaries = T_{p-1} (triangular numbers)
   M(5,6): 10=V(Petersen), M(7,8): 21=H_forb_2, M(9,10): 36=|Phi+(E6)|

2. ADE MODULAR INVARIANTS: E_n invariant at p = h(E_n)
   E6 at p=12=h(E6), E7 at p=18=h(E7), E8 at p=30=h(E8)

3. CENTRAL CHARGES: ratios of tournament numbers
   Ising: c=1/KEY1, Potts: c=KEY1^2/KEY_SUM
   tri-critical: c=H_forb_1/V(Petersen)

4. CONFORMAL DIMENSIONS of M(5,6) include:
   h=KEY2/KEY1=3/2=perfect fifth, h=H_forb_1/V(Pet)=7/10

5. FIBONACCI ANYONS: d_tau = phi = (1+sqrt(KEY_SUM))/KEY1
   Quantum dimension involves sqrt(KEY_SUM)

6. T_4 = 10 = T(4): triangular numbers and (2,3)-trees AGREE at k=4!

7. THE c=1 BARRIER: total 'room' for minimal models = KEY1 = 2
   Sum of all deficits = KEY1

8. MODULAR S-MATRIX involves sqrt(KEY1) (Ising), sqrt(KEY_SUM) (Potts)

THE DEEP LESSON:
  Every CFT datum — central charge, conformal dimension, fusion coefficient,
  quantum dimension, modular invariant classification — is built from
  {KEY1=2, KEY2=3, KEY_SUM=5, H_forb=7} and their square roots.
  The (2,3) universe IS conformal field theory.
